<br>
I'm going to have to disagree that light tanks are worse off than other tanks.  In my expierience of the realm of Hibernia, I have learned that a high RR Blademaster is probably the best tank in the game.  They have insane evade, good armor, and all their Realm abilities are at tank costs!  While I do think their styles could use some work (along with all of Hibernias styles), the underlying factor of how well you do in RvR is not determined by your damage.  It is determined by your survivability!  <br>
<br>
Don't even get me started on Berzerkers.  If there is ONE class that is designed to do damage it is the Berzerker.  Their styles are among the best in the game.  They get a lesser evade, but its better than nothing.  IMO, Evade 3 is enough combined with parry given their damage capabilities.<br>
<br>
I don't know much about mercenaries, but I hear that their style options are good too.  Only Evade one, but they get chain <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Heres my take on the issue.  Blademasters could use some style loving but are a really great class, especially when they hit higher RRs and double swing just about as much as a Zerker does <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Zerkers are currently the most damaging of the light tanks, at the expense of lower defense.  However, since the nerf, the zerker relies simply on superior styles as a mechanism of doing more damage. Thus, when the upcoming style review is passed, we might discover that a revamped style system gives each of the three light tanks comparable damage.  In such a case we will observe that the zerker was overnerfed, and the class would need a damage increase to bring their damage back to par.<br>
<br>
Mercenaries get chain, and good styles from what I hear.  I suppose they fall somewhere in the middle.  Dirty Tricks is also a great ability IMO.  Don't know much about this class <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thats my take on the issue.  Plz let me know what you think.<br>
<br>
Btw I posted this in the zerker section probably just because I play a zerker.<br>
